label chapter11:

    # [Scene: Saltwren Commons | Dawn — hours after the storm]

    scene bg ch9_3be532_1 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Distant generator thrum; shouted orders; the steady staccato of rain still on canvas]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Aggressive, pulsing strings — urgent, relentless]
    "You wake to other people's exhaustion: the low, animal chorus of people who have spent a night moving things they cannot yet measure. Your hands smell of salt and diesel; the copper bracelet at your wrist"
    "is cool with rain. Beneath the mud and the broken stakes, seedlings you planted with Rae are half-buried and clinging to their soil like small, stubborn flags."
    "Tommy is on the boardwalk, sleeves rolled, shouting into a handheld radio. His face is raw in the gray light; the lines at his mouth look deeper. He meets your eyes and for a second his expression is only: What now?"
    "You already know. The pump array you helped reroute last night held for some of the Old Quarter but failed in others. The contract you signed at that polished desk — Celeste Park's money — bought"
    "machines and crews, and where the machines went, it made a difference. Where they didn't, the town woke with new wounds: basement furniture bobbing in soup, a row of framed photos stuck to cardboard, a grandmother"
    "wrapped in a tarp and trembling while neighbors pile canned goods at her feet."
    "You move with the urgency that has been bred into you — fast hands, short breaths — because there is no time for the grief that wants to find you. There is only triage."
    "Rae appears carrying a camera, mud on her knees, eyes bright and ferocious. She doesn't look away when she sees the half-buried planters."
    show rae_carter at left:
        zoom 0.7

    rae_carter "They're sending a camera truck downtown. We can get footage of the affected blocks—people need to see the scale. Also—' (she swallows) '—they're forming a list for temporary housing."
    show mara_lin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_lin "Good. Start a column for medical needs. Tommy, can you pull volunteers to the Old Quarter? Elias Navarro—' (you turn and find him at the edge of the Commons, rain on his collar, a weathered legal pad in hand)— '—get Dr. Bhatt to the sewage pumps. We need diagnostics, not just buckets."
    "Elias Navarro crosses the boardwalk to you. He smells like wet wool and something cleaner — the scent of someone who still carries a suit inside the rain jacket, even here."
    show elias_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_navarro "I already spoke to Amina. She's compiling sediment samples. We can patch the suction lines, but the rebar in the promenade's foundation is compromised—"

    mara_lin "We don't need the architecture of the pitch. We need people out of floodplains and food in stomachs. Right now, numbers and nuance come later."

    elias_navarro "I know. I'm—I've been on calls all night. The cooperative's legal team thinks we need to document, fast. If we don't show compliance, Celeste Park's waiver could be pulled, and crews stop coming."
    "Mara Lin: (he opens his mouth, then closes it) 'So we save funds by cutting corners on neighborhoods.'"
    "Elias Navarro is the kind of man who builds bridges with diagrams; when diagrams collide with people's faces, his patience frays into guilt."

    menu:
        "Jog to the Old Quarter to help people move heavier items":
            "You shoulder a soaked crate and feel the sweet, punishing burn in your arms. A child clings to your calves as a neighbor thanks you between sobs."
        "Stay at the Commons to coordinate logistics and paperwork":
            "You hunch over a soggy laptop under a tarp, fingers numb. A volunteer calls for water and you map supplies, bloodless but effective."

    menu:
        "Call out the cooperative's culpability by naming neighborhoods that were left without pumps":
            "Your voice snaps like a live wire. A hush falls as you list streets, faces; a woman in the back keens, and a camera focuses on you with unblinking lens."
        "Demand immediate binding protections and a public audit before crews continue":
            "You present a list of demands, your hands steady for the first time all day. Some officials shift uncomfortably; others nod, calculating. The legal counselor makes notes."

    menu:
        "Ask Elias to hand over all internal correspondence to independent counsel":
            "He hesitates, the lines around his eyes deepening. 'It could cost me my job,' he says, the confession heavier than the papers. He slides one folder across the table."
        "Tell Elias you'll publicize what you have and let the pressure force transparency":
            "He looks at you with an expression both afraid and proud. 'You're willing to burn bridges,' he says quietly. 'Then do it.'"
    "THE END"
    # [GAME END]
    return
